[Benefits, efficacy, and risk associated with the conventional treatment of 
obesity: should we treat the weight excess?].

[Article in Spanish]

Salas i Salvadó J(1).

Author information:
(1)Unidad de Nutrición, Hospital Universitari de Sant Joan de Reus, Universitat 
Rovira i Virgili, Reus, España. jss@fmcs.urv.es

The literature contains a large number of published articles indicating a strong 
relationship between obesity and morbidity-mortality due to different cause. 
There are also various short- to medium-term studies demonstrating the benefits 
of a moderate weight loss on the control of obesity-related risk factors. 
Nonetheless, very few studies have attempted to define the potential medium- to 
long-term morbidity/mortality benefits associated with weight loss using 
conventional obesity treatment methods. This review attempts to weigh up the 
benefits and also the risks associated with the methods currently recognized for 
the treatment of this pathology. We also attempt to analyze the efficacy of 
these methods for controlling body weight in the medium and long term, as this 
is essential when it comes to advising the obese population.

