our series of femoral-based hemodialysis grafts is comparable with rates 
reported in the literature for upper extremity polytetrafluoroethylene 
angioaccess grafts. Although not considered a first choice, femoral artery-based 
hemodialysis access is a viable option when arteriovenous fistulae in the upper 
extremity cannot be constructed.

